-Chaining#{6}":[118,118],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{7}":[119,119],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{8}":[120,120],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{9}":[121,121],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{10}":[122,123],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{11}":[124,124],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{12}":[125,125],"#74HC595 8-Bit Shift Register — Serial to Parallel (DIP-16)#Daisy-Chaining#{13}":[126,127]},"outlinks":[{"title":"passives","target":"passives","line":3},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":3},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":29},{"title":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","target":"arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb","line":29},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":29},{"title":"dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":29},{"title":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":29},{"title":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","target":"esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3","line":29},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":29},{"title":"osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v","target":"osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v","line":29},{"title":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","target":"raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3","line":29},{"title":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","target":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","line":43},{"title":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","target":"arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b","line":114},{"title":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","target":"arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts","line":115},{"title":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","target":"nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3","line":116},{"title":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","target":"elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb","line":117},{"title":"4-digit-7-segment-display-hs420561k-common-cathode","target":"4-digit-7-segment-display-hs420561k-common-cathode","line":118},{"title":"5161as-single-digit-7-segment-led-display-red-common-cathode","target":"5161as-single-digit-7-segment-led-display-red-common-cathode","line":119},{"title":"1088as-8x8-red-led-dot-matrix-common-cathode-3mm","target":"1088as-8x8-red-led-dot-matrix-common-cathode-3mm","line":120},{"title":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","target":"max7219-spi-led-driver-controls-8-digits-or-8x8-matrix-with-3-pins","line":121},{"title":"dk-electronics-hw-130-motor-shield-uses-l293d-at-600ma","target":"dk-electronics-hw-130-motor-shield-uses-l293d-at-600ma","line":122},{"title":"passives","target":"passives","line":125},{"title":"shields","target":"shields","line":126}],"metadata":{"description":"8-bit serial-to-parallel shift register — 3 GPIO pins in, 8 digital outputs. Daisy-chainable for 16, 24, 32+ outputs. 2-6V operating range. The classic IO expander for LED arrays, 7-segment displays, and any situation where you're running out of pins","topics":["[[passives]]","[[shields]]"],"status":"needs-test","quantity":0,"voltage":[2,3.3,5],"interfaces":["SPI-like"],"logic_level":"Matches VCC (2-6V)","manufacturer":"Various (TI, NXP, ON Semi)","part_number":"74HC595","pinout":"74HC595 DIP-16:\nPin 1  (QB)    → Output B (bit 1)\nPin 2  (QC)    → Output C (bit 2)\nPin 3  (QD)    → Output D (bit 3)\nPin 4  (QE)    → Output E (bit 4)\nPin 5  (QF)    → Output F (bit 5)\nPin 6  (QG)    → Output G (bit 6)\nPin 7  (QH)    → Output H (bit 7)\nPin 8  (GND)   → Ground\nPin 9  (QH')   → Serial data out (to next 595's SER pin for daisy-chaining)\nPin 10 (SRCLR) → Shift register clear (active LOW, tie to VCC for normal operation)\nPin 11 (SRCLK) → Shift register clock (clock pulse shifts data in)\nPin 12 (RCLK)  → Storage register clock / latch (pulse HIGH to update outputs)\nPin 13 (OE)    → Output enable (active LOW, tie to GND for always-on)\nPin 14 (SER)   → Serial data input (from MCU or previous 595)\nPin 15 (QA)    → Output A (bit 0)\nPin 16 (VCC)   → 2-6V power\n","compatible_with":["[[arduino-mega-2560-is-a-54-io-5v-board-with-4-hardware-uarts]]","[[nodemcu-esp32s-is-a-dual-core-wifi-bt-mcu-with-34-gpio-at-3v3]]","[[arduino-uno-r3-is-a-14-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-usb-b]]","[[elegoo-mega-2560-r3-is-an-arduino-mega-clone-with-ch340-usb]]","[[arduino-nano-v3-is-a-22-io-5v-board-with-atmega328p-and-mini-usb]]","[[dccduino-nano-is-an-arduino-nano-clone-with-ch340-usb]]","[[osepp-uno-r3-plus-is-an-arduino-uno-clone-at-5v]]","[[raspberry-pi-pico-is-an-rp2040-mcu-with-26-gpio-at-3v3]]","[[esp8266-nodemcu-amica-is-a-wifi-mcu-with-11-io-at-3v3]]"],"used_in":[],"warnings":["Outputs can source/sink ~6mA per pin at 5V — enough for LEDs with resistors, NOT for motors or relays. Use a ULN2003 or MOSFET for higher current","OE pin (pin 13) is active LOW — tie to GND for normal operation, or connect to a PWM pin for brightness control of all outputs simultaneously","SRCLR (pin 10) is active LOW — tie to VCC or outputs will stay cleared","Maximum output current for entire chip is 70mA — if driving 8 LEDs, keep each under ~8mA","Daisy-chaining adds propagation delay — clock all data in, then pulse latch once to update all outputs simultaneously"],"datasheet_url":"https://www.ti.com/product/SN74HC595"},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[[76,99],[103,107]],"key":"docs/parts/74hc595-8-bit-shift-register-serial-to-parallel-dip16.md"},
